  "title": "Research Fellow (Advanced construction and sustainability)",
  "description": "<p>Interested applicants are invited to apply directly at the <a href=\"https://careers.nus.edu.sg/job/Research-Fellow-%28Advanced-construction-and-sustainability%29/31524-en_GB/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>NUS\nCareer Portal</strong></a></p><p>Your application will be processed only if you apply\nvia <a href=\"https://careers.nus.edu.sg/job/Research-Fellow-%28Advanced-construction-and-sustainability%29/31524-en_GB/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>NUS\nCareer Portal</strong></a></p><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.<br /></p><h2><strong>Job Description</strong></h2><p>The National University of Singapore (NUS) invites applications for a postdoctoral Research Fellow position in advanced construction and sustainability. The successful applicant will work under the supervision of Asst Prof Meng Xin from the Department of Civil and Environmental Engineering. <br />This position is part of an exciting research programme aimed at advancing the strategic adoption of metal additive manufacturing in construction for decarbonisation. </p><p><br />The Research Fellow is expected to:<br />•    Conduct novel and impactful research in the areas of life-cycle carbon and cost analysis, 3D printed hybrid structural systems, and construction sustainability.<br />•    Disseminate research findings through high-quality journal papers and presentations at international conferences.<br />•    Support the supervision and mentoring of PhD students.<br />•    Contribute to teaching, funding applications, and outreach activities. </p><h2><strong>Job Requirements</strong></h2><p><br />•    Possess a PhD in civil engineering.<br />•    Demonstrates a strong background in civil engineering research and publications.<br />•    Must have expertise in structural design and life-cycle carbon and cost analysis.<br />•    Must have excellent communication and collaboration skills.<br />•    Preferably with knowledge of metal 3D printing and hybrid construction.<br />•    Preferably with knowledge and skills in AI.<br />•    Open to fixed-term contract.</p>",
